Description: Vasolux Microsystems develops optically based medical devices.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: VasoLux MicroSystems, LLC (www.vasolux.com) has developed a novel diagnostic imaging system to help surgeons identify later-stage osteoarthritis patients who are best suited for cartilage repair procedures or joint replacement surgery. Osteoarthritis – a condition caused by the degradation of cartilage – is considered one of the leading causes of chronic disability worldwide and affects more than 20 million people in the U.S. alone. VasoLux’s technology quantitatively assesses the quality of cartilage, in vivo, in a non-destructive, minimally invasive procedure. Competing procedures and technologies, such as arthroscopy, MRI, CT, Ultrasound, OCT, and X-ray cannot provide physicians with an objective measurement capable of identifying the early progression of osteoarthritis, determining the true extent of a cartilage defect, or evaluating the quality of regenerated cartilage. Consequently, physicians lack the information needed to select the appropriate therapeutic intervention or revise their treatment plan if prior efforts have not reinvigorated the cartilage or prevented its degeneration. VasoLux’s diagnostic imaging system eliminates the subjective diagnoses of osteoarthritis, which in turn reduces inefficiencies in the health care system.
Industry Groups: Data and Analytics, Health Care, Software

Description: Mobile Technology Association of Michigan is a non-profit trade association for Michigan’s mobile and wireless technology industries.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Detroit Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Mobile Technology Association of Michigan (MTAM) is a non-profit trade association for Michigan’s mobile and wireless (connected) technologies; firms that are providing those technologies and firms - in all industries - that are utilizing those technologies.  MTAM performs research for members and other interested parties; facilitates idea sharing, entrepreneurial programs, training programs, and jobs creation; acts as a liaison with the connected technology community inside and outside of Michigan; and serves as a resource for all things related to mobile and wireless (connected) technologies.  The organization also enables Michigan-based growth of the international Mobile Monday organization through its subsidiary, Mobile Monday Michigan which boasts 3000+ members in chapters located in Ann Arbor, Detroit, Grand Rapids and Lansing. The Mission of MTAM includes: - Facilitating collaboration between varied sectors of the connected tech eco-system and other non-tech industries in order to drive innovation and opportunities involving these technologies - To increase the use of, and demand for, Michigan-based mobile/wireless (connected) technology products and services in-state, nationally and globally - To diversify Michigan's economy thru the growth of connected technologies-enabled innovation in industries that otherwise would remain stagnant - To increase the productivity and profitability of every industry vertical in Michigan via the use of these technologies - To create sustainable jobs and increased entrepreneurial opportunities in the state based on the use of these technologies, thereby achieving substantial growth of Michigan's economy - To help the communities we serve via the use of these technologies Mobile Technology Association of Michigan was founded in 2010 and is based in Detroit, Michigan.

Full Description: McDonnell Law Group is a Silicon Valley-based law firm serving the legal needs of high-tech and consumer goods businesses, ranging from entrepreneurial start-ups to public companies.  Our attorneys have served as General Counsel of tech companies and have significant private practice experience representing venture-backed and public companies from formation through liquidity events. McDonnell Law Group provides three main types of legal services to its clients: 1. Outsourced General Counsel Services  2. Licensing and Corporate Transactions  3. In-house Legal Support  We tailor our legal services to meet your legal needs, whether those needs are for contract drafting and negotiating or for more involved management of the legal function.   Our legal services include regular presentations on areas of particular interest to you, such as reviews of advertising law requirements, open source management, and license structures.  When we engage a new client, we offer a no-charge review that includes:  1.  examination of the client's corporate history, legal form agreements, and material contracts 2.  interviews with senior management for a detailed understanding of the objectives of the business 3.  meetings with the client's existing corporate, IP, and HR legal counsel, if any Our objective is to get up to speed on your legal needs without cost to you so that we can thereafter provide cost-efficient, informed legal services.  Feel free to contact us at info@mcdlg.com.

Description: News and resources about entrepreneurship across Nebraska.
Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US
Full Description: Nebraska Entrepreneurship was created by the University of Nebraska to support entrepreneurship education, training and outreach.  It serves as a resource to Nebraska and tells the stories of entrepreneurs at the University and throughout Nebraska, highlighting their contributions to the state. Entrepreneurship isn’t easy. The innovation required to spearhead a new business or idea often means entrepreneurs are treading ground where few — if any — have ventured before. Anyone who has ever taken the plunge into the entrepreneurial world can tell you the ever-changing marketplace presents a lot of challenges. They felt there was a need for a central hub to connect entrepreneurs, and to make them aware of the community resources available to help their businesses thrive. To that end, NebraskaEntrepreneurship.com was created. Through their business profiles, entrepreneurial news and growing video archive, they hope to be the first place Nebraska’s entrepreneurs stop on their way to achieving their goals. And, through helping entrepreneurs, they hope to further the economic development and workforce goals of the University of Nebraska and their state.

Description: Career matching service
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: StrictlyTalent is a confidential and niche based matching tool that links both recruiters and employees with meaningful career relationships.  ST has been described as an Eharmony like tool for career seeking professionals and recruiters. This system attracts the top 30% of talent as well as great opportunities and then matches them together by a profiling algorithm.  Through this new way of recruiting and job searching, employees no longer have to send their resumes to a black hole. Often a high level professional is not in the position to openly seek future employment, StrictlyTalent provides the confidentiality to do that. On the other hand, recruiters, hiring managers, and HR waste a lot of time receiving resumes from unqualified candidates. StrictlyTalent will not show the user-base which jobs and companies are in the system and even after a match is made, the relationship has to be requested and accepted by both parties to move forward.  StrictlyTalent does not claim to be the full solution, rather the initial platform or filter. The concept is to proactively manage a career and proactively recruit rather than reactionary actions when it's absolutely necessary.  Currently StrictlyTalent hosts two networks; StrictlyExecs (a network just for executive level positions) and StrictlyClosers (a network geared to high level sales and marketing professionals).  StrictlyWebDev and StrictlyITPros are the next networks that will be offered by StrictlyTalent.com
